:44','2012-07-25 20:53:44','<h2>Create Your Model</h2>\r\n\r\nIf you\'re new to SolidWorks, check out the video below on creating a simple bone wrench. \r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/46383997\" width=\"550\" height=\"327\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>\r\n\r\nOnce you complete your model, you\'ll want to keep in mind that when you export a SolidWorks file only solid bodies will be exported for STL files and whatever is visible will be exported for a VRML file (full color). When working with parts with small features or wall thicknesses you want to make sure that you adhere to the limitations of the material that you want to print in. The <a href=\"http://www.shapeways.com/materials/material-options\" title=\"Material Options\">Material Options</a> gives you guidelines for the parameters that you\'ll need to meet for each materal.\r\n\r\n<h2>Upload Your Model</h2>\r\nOnce you have your model prepped and ready for upload, you can upload it in several ways. For models that are not going to be printed in full color, you\'ll be uploading a STL file. This can be done manually by doing a save-as STL and uploading the file to Shapeways, or you can use the <a href=\"http://www.shapeways.com/tutorials/solid_works_add-in\" title=\"ShapeWays Add-In\">Shapeways Add-In</a> for SolidWorks. With either of these options, you need to set the resolution first before saving the file out. The resolution can be found under \"options\" from the save-as dialog box.\r\n\r\nFor full color parts, you\'ll need to save the file out as a VRML file and then upload directly to Shapeways. In the save-as options for VRML, the output format needs to be set to VRML 97 or the upload will fail. The resolution for VRML files can be set by changing the image quality, tools>options>document properties>image quality. Check out the video below for a full explanation for both file types\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/46383998\" width=\"550\" height=\"327\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>','Prepping and Uploading a model with SolidWorks','','publish','open','open','','prepping-and-uploading-a-model-with-solidworks','','','2012-07-25 13:54:40','2012-07-25 20:54:40','',0,'http://swztest.solidwize.com/?p=662',0,'post','',0),(721,15,'2012-08-30 15:48:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-08-30 15:48:45','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://swztest.solidwize.com/?p=721',0,'post','',0),(722,2,'2012-08-30 15:54:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-08-30 15:54:07','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://swztest.solidwize.com/?p=722',0,'post','',0),(723,100,'2012-09-06 04:44:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2012-09-06 04:44:49','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://swztest.solidwize.com/?p=723',0,'post','',0),(645,15,'2012-07-15 13:42:23','2012-07-15 20:42:23','[ion_tabset tab1=\"Tab1\"]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab1\"]<strong>hello</strong>\r\n<p style=\"float: right;\">rawr!!!</p>\r\n[/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[/ion_tabset]\r\n\r\n[ion_tabset tab1=\"Hehe\" tab2=\"hoohoo\" tab3=\"dude\"]\r\n\r\n[subscribebar text=\"Get immediate access to the entire library!\" color=\"blue\" btntext=\"Become a Member »\"]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab1\"][videodirectory id=\"17,13\" ][/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab2\"]aw<a href=\"http://html.com\">asdf</a>[/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab3\"]asdfasdf[/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[/ion_tabset]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[ion_tabset tab1=\"asdf\" tab2=\"asdf\" tab3=\"asdf\"]\r\n\r\n[email text=\"Get immediate access to the entire library!\" color=\"blue\" btntext=\"Become a Member »\" usertype=\"author\"]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab1\"][videodirectory id=\"7,14\" ][/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab2\"]asdf<a href=\"http://download.com\">asdf</a>[/ion_tab]\r\n\r\n[ion_tab id=\"tab3